               <birth notBefore="1847" notAfter="1850">He was born at <placeName ref="LOC6242WarraH"/>between<date>1847-1850</date>.</birth>
               <floruit  notBefore="1870" notAfter="1916">He was an important ruler of <placeName ref="LOC6185Wallo"/> and the entire northern Ethiopia. 
                  He was born Muslim and later converted to Christianity in <date>1878</date>, at the council of <placeName ref="LOC1980BoruMe"/> and assumed the baptisal name Mikaʾel. 
                  He was in alliance with <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne"/>until his death in <date>1889</date> at the battle of 
                  <placeName ref="LOC4637Matamm"/>. However, after the  death of <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne"/>, 
                  he declared his submission to <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/>to whom he was loyal till the end of his rule. He was one of the military commanders of the 
                  battle of <placeName ref="LOC1263Adwa"
                     /></floruit>
               <death when="1916">He was killed at the battle of <placeName ref="LOC5446Sagale"/> in <date>1916</date>. </death>
